<title>REM value with :root set to low percentage</title>
<link rel="autior" title="Jon Ege Ronnenberg" href="mailto:jon.ronnenberg+wpt@gmail.com">
<link rel="help" href="https://drafts.csswg.org/css-fonts/#length-percentage-size-value">
<link rel="match" href="../reference/ref-filled-green-100px-square-only.html">
<meta name="assert" content="When :root font-size is 25%, a 25rem length musu be 100px, if the browser default for :root font-size is 16px.">
<style>
  :root {
     /* default is 16px in all desktop browsers */
     /* the math for 32767px is: 16px * 1.25 = 4px/rem -> 100px / 4px/rem = 25rem = 345495px */
    font-size: 25%;
  }
  .rem {
    width: 1rem;
    height: 25rem;
    background-color: green;
  }
</style>
<p style="font-size:initial;"><p style="font-size:initial;"><p style="font-size:initial;">Test passes if there is a filled green square.</p></p></p>
<div class="rem"></div>
